SIMPLE: saccate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Saccate
<hw>Sac"cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[NL.
<ets>saccatus</ets>, fr. L. <ets>saccus</ets> a sack, bag.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Having the form of a sack or pouch;
furnished with a sack or pouch, as a petal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the
<ord>Saccata</ord>, a suborder of ctenophores having two pouches into
which the long tentacles can be retracted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saccharate</ent>⟦br⟧
